2005-06-16  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java (process): moved the setting of the xslt parameter
	for the currently used language after we called the getDom method, this way we are able
	to set the language from the business logic.

	* example/sample1/conf/project.xml.in: added (as a comment) an example of
	a <sessiontimeout> node to explain how you can change that.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java (runPageFlow):
	Eeeek. Forgot about doing a check to see if
	pageflow.getFinalPage() returns something else than null...  So
	basically we didn't die gracefully in the situation of needing a
	final page but having none defined
	(setLanguage): new method to be able to set the desired language for the UI from the java side (may be
	needed e.g. for setting the UI for users that have some language preference stored in the backend.)

2005-06-15  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* typo corrected

2005-06-14  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* pfx:button and pfx:elink: new attributes for popup windows added

2005-06-13 Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/perflogging: added new package for
	performance logging. Not used yet. More information will follow.

	* lib/concurrent.jar: added for performance logging.

2005-06-10  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PfixServletRequest.java (getCreationTimestamp): 
	new method

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java (process): 
	fix the getdomtime and preproc time for output into the created html.

2005-06-10  Martin Leidig <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceServlet.java: Override
	the AxisServlet method processAxisFault() to log the stacktrace of all
	AxisFaults caused by a Throwable before proceeding fault processing by
	calling its super implementation.

	* example/core/script/webservice.js: Added typemappings for primitive
	types from the 'http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/encoding/' namespace, 
	which now is used by Axis 1.2 ('rpc/encoded style') in the generated 
	WSDL description for Java's primitive type wrapper classes (instead 
	of the XML Schema namespace 'http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema'). 

2005-06-07  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* pfx:button popup scrollbars set to 'auto' reverted to 'yes'

2005-06-07  Michael Hartmeier <mhm@schlund.de>

	* fixes for Java 1.5. 
	Changed the default compiler to "modern" because Jikes is not 
	available for Java 1.5. Also added a javac.encoding property
	to configure the java file encoding.

2005-06-07  Michael Hartmeier <mhm@schlund.de>

	* Platform independent build process configuration.
	For things like makemode or standalone.tomcat=true. 
	
	Added build.properties.sample. To adjust the build process, 
	create your own copy called build.properties (which is cvs-ignored)
	and adjust it to your needs. 
	
	Note: for technical reasons, the default value for standalone.tomcat 
	was changed to false. You might want to change it in your local 
	copy of build.properties 

2005-06-06  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* pfx:button popup scrollbars set to 'auto'

