2005-04-24  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependencyManager.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/AuxDependency.java: 
	Completely rewrote the way the parent-child relation of auxdependencies are stored.
	we now store the childs seperate for each themes spec. Also the affected targets are stored locally 
	in the AuxDependency itself, so no need anymore to store a link to the parent.
	Basically all of this should fix a bug that has been there forever, but only with the new variants 
	happens much more often.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/PageTargetTree.java (getPageInfoForPageName): new method
	(addEntry): now store also a mapping of page name to all pageinfos with that name (aka all variants)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerator.java: 
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetFactory.java: 
	all Target creation now needs a themes argument. Use the new Themes type.

