2004-12-27  Daniel Hopp <daniel.hopp@schlund.de>

	* Minor changes to the templates pfx:image and pfx:xinp[@type='image'] in
	~/pfixcore/example/core/xsl/include.xsl.in and
	~/pfixcore/example/core/xsl/forminput.xsl.in:
	The 'alt'-attribute was added as xsl:param as well as an optional
	parameter called 'exclude-attributes', which contains a string of
	attribute names, _not_ to copy from context-node into the resulting
	img/input-element.
	'border="0"' removed from output-elements img/input[type=image], cause it's
	deprecated according to HTML 4.01 specification.

2004-12-21  Ute Platzer <up@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultAuthIWrapperState.java: in getDocument()
	method, use super.createDefaultResultDocument() instead of creating a new ResultDocument.

2004-12-21  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/TempFile.java: (Added) Temporary file implementation,
	which ensures that the associated physical file is deleted, when the object is no longer
	in use, i.e. when it gets finalized by the garbage collector.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/FileData.java: Removed deletion, which now is done
	via the assigned TempFile instance.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartHandler.java: Instead of java.io.File now
	the new TempFile class is used for representing file parts.

2004-12-20  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/FileData.java: Associated temporary files now are
	deleted when object gets finalized.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/multipart/MultipartHandler.java: Temporary files exceeding the
	size limit now are deleted immediately.


2004-12-17  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/IWrapperSimpleContainer.java:
	implemented the "false" value for the pfx:command
	SUGGESTCONT. This will stop the IWrapperContainer from ever
	suggesting to advance in the pageflow. This is somewhat similar to
	the forcestop=true attribute, but it only works for
	DefaultIWrapperStates, while forcestop works regardless of the State. The difference
	bvetween the two is, that using SUGGESTCONT=false will still call retrieveCurrentStatus() on
	all Handlers in the group of Handlers selected by SELWRP (or all if there's no SELWRP used)
	and all Handlers that have alwaysretrieve set to "true" in the property file.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: starwithflow will
	now use the pageattribute to stop at that page in any case. That
	means, if the page is part of the pageflow that's checked, it will
	not be checked for needsData() past this page, but instead stopped
	there in any case. If the page is not part of the pageflow, it
	will be used instead of a possibly given final page.

2004-12-16  Niels Schelbach <niels@schlund.de>
        * example/core/build/iwrapper.xsl:
        * src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor/handlers/EditUserDataHandler.java: Changed generation of
        iwrapper, so that paramnames are first letter uppercased for get set methods. Following
        common java bean convention.

2004-12-14  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* skel/build.xml:
	"clean-project": do not fail if there is no dir.webapps
	"clean-jni": do not fail if there is no dir.jni

2004-12-13  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: Changed the way a pageflow continuation is started. Now the default
	ist to always start a flow, unless context.prohibitContinue() has been called (from the State or a ContextRessource).
	removed some methods that are shouldn't be accessible from the outside anyway (getJumpToPage, getJumpToPageFlow).
	The PageMessage methods no longer have the error argument, such a situation can now be signalled via prohibitContinue().

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ResultDocument.java: setContinue(), wantsContinue() REMOVED. ResultDocument is
	no longer used to signal the continuation of a pageflow, it's the default now that has to be explicitely prohibited
	by calling context.prohibitContinue() anywhere during a request cycle.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/StateImpl.java (renderContextResources): new protected method.
	Descendants can call this to get the default handling (aka: inserting) of ContextResources.
	(addResponseHeadersAndType): new protected method. Can be used to get default handling of headers and mime type.
	(createDefaultResultDocument): uses both renderContextResources and addResponseHeadersAndType.
	This is the prime candidate for descendants to get a new ResultDocument.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/StaticState.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultAuthIWrapperState.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor/handlers/SessionManagerState.java: Changed to use context.prohibitContinue()
	at the right places.

	* example/core/xsl/navigation.xsl.in:
	* example/core/xsl/forminput.xsl.in: <pfx:button>, <pfx:xinp
	  type="submit|image"> new attributes: @pageflow, @jumptopage,
	  @jumptopageflow, @forcestop. Also new pfx:commands: DESELWRP, SUGGESTCONT

2004-12-07  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* xdocs/**: updated documentation
	* skel/build.xml:
	"check-permissions":
	finally changed to make all .sh files executable within dir.projects.
	"tomcat.dir.opt":
	make tomcat extract if there's no dir.tomcat/bin/catalina.sh instead of
	tomcat dir only; works around cvs empty dir bug on pristine checked out
	projects
	"clean-project":
	deletion of **/WEB-INF/web.xml

