	the displayed value of the link and urlencode the value used in
	the href. Thanks to Sebastian Marsching for the report. I hope
	this fixes the possible problem...

2004-11-22  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added client-side support of RPC/Literal encoding. Improved special
	character handling.

	* example/core/script/webservice.js: Encoding style and use now
	can be set at SOAP_Call objects via the setEncoding() method. The
	serialize() method of the serializer base class SOAP_SimpleSerializer
	and all derived classes now has an additional argument for passing
	a SOAP_SerializeCtx object, which represents the current serialization
	context and gives access to data needed during the serialization
	process (like the encoding use). Also improved special character
	handling: the XML_Writer method writeChars() now writes forbidden
	characters as entities.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Wsdl2Js.java: Encoding
	style and use information now is read from the WSDL description and
	transformed into according SOAP_Call setEncoding() statements within
	the webservice stub methods.

2004-11-18  J�rg H�cker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/email/EmailSender.java


2004-11-17  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: added the ability to
	specify in a new created session that it doesn't use cookies
	despite what the browser sends. This helps with situations where
	the test cookie is there, but the secure cookie has been
	denied. Fixed two code paths that seem to be affected by this.

2004-11-13  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: fix javadoc

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: added the ability to specify with a property to NOT enforce a cookie check
	despite the session being marked already as using cookies. This is ONLY to cope with broken clients.

2004-11-11  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java:
	make sure that when the context returns true for
	pageMessageIsError() we add all the needed info to the resdoc

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: Pagemessages now
	take another argument "iserror". If any pagemessage is supplied
	with this argument set to true, the Context will not enter the
	pageflow but will stay on the current page (much like it does in
	the case of an error).

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextCounterImpl.java:
	* example/core/xsl/include.xsl.in:
	* example/core/txt/styles.xml: cosmetics, implement example

2004-11-09  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: remove the __foreceauth reg param again. For now, we better
	try to re-auth just everytime we get a direct submit with __sendingauthdata set to 'true'.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: more security stuff. Now we allow more than one secure
	session again by not only using one cookie, but instead naming the cookie according to the associated session
	(until now, the cookie was called __PFIX_SECURE_SESS__, now it's called __PFIX_SEC_<Session-Id>)

2004-11-08  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: added __forceauth
	parameter to force a re-authentication.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/AuthenticationHandler.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/DirectOutputServlet.java:
	change calls to checkAuthorization to supply "false" as forceauth argument.

2004-11-05  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* started 0.8.3-pre

	* released 0.8.2

2004-11-04  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* example/core/build/create_apacheconf.xsl:
	Implemented filtering out of duplicate Alias (<passthrough>) directives.

2004-10-31  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: final pieces in the security work: now we mark a session when it's used with a cookie
	enabled client and invalidate it whenever a later request doesn't supply cookies anymore.  This defeats clients who were
	able to get a foreign secure session id and try to work around the cookie based security features outlined below.

2004-10-29  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: bug fix: make it
	work without cookies again: we actually have to believe that the
	session is secure (if it is marked as such) when a request doesn't
	supply cookies at all.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PfixServletRequest.java: removed the pagemessage stuff...
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: ...and moved it here completely.
	implemented the handling of args for pagemessages

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ResultDocument.java (createIncludeFromStatusCode): made static as I need it
	from Context where I have no ResultDocument instance... a bit hackish. fixed all instances where it's used.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/ContextCounterImpl.java: moved pagemessage setting to the CR, as it handles more
	cases of changing the counter value

	* example/common/dyntxt/statusmessages.xml: removed the "warning" attribute. It no longer makes sense.

	* example/core/txt/styles.xml:
	* example/core/script/baselib.js:
	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_order.xml:
	* example/core/xsl/utils.xsl.in: remove progressbar stuff.

2004-10-28  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_order.xml:
	* example/sample1/txt/pages/main_overview.xml: both pages can display warnings now

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java: consolidated the addPageMessage to
	have addPageMessage(Scode), addPageMessage(Scode, Level), addPageMessage(Scode, Level, Args[]).
	(insertPageMessages): Still more work to do to handle arguments at all....

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PfixServletRequest.java: only one
	addPageMessage(Scode, Level, Args[]) method.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/CounterHandler.java: changed accordingly

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: More security related work.
	The ServletManager will now prohibit the following cases:
	- A valid secure session is used but the request was not made under SSL
	- A valid secure session is used and the browser handles cookies but
	the __PFIX_SECURE_SSL_SESS__ cookie isn't found or it doesn't match the session id.

	Both cases will result in the secure session being invalidated.

2004-10-28  Benjamin Reitzammer  <benjamin@schlund.de>

	* Implemented the new pagemessages feature: Context has several new methods
	called addPageMessage(). With these you can associate a Statuscode with the
	next displayed page, no matter which page this is (this works with all
	pageflow/jumptopage stuff pustefix can do). Depending on the level, that's
	supplied with the StatusCode, the StatusCodes are wrapped in an according
	CSS class and a header is displayed too.
	To finally show the messages on a page, simply include use the <pfx:pagemessages />
	tag anywhere on your page, where you want messages to be shown.
	Take a look at the Context's Javadoc for details how to add StatusCodes
	to pages.

