2004-10-08  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java:
	constructParameters now needs to get the session, too. This is
	used to contruct another parameter called __external_session_ref
	which holds the normal session id when not running under SSL and
	the invalid insecure "parent" session when running under SSL. This
	id can be used to give to the outside for jumping back into the
	application.

	* example/core/xsl/master.xsl.in: add the ixsl:param __external_session_ref.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: debug output fixed

2004-10-08  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionhandler/ExceptionContext.java:
	bugfix: ignore all exceptions when createing sessiondump. If exceptions
	occur, try to report them properly.

2004-10-06  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	* example/core/xsl/include.xsl.in: Added template for generating
	webservice console, which creates links to some webservice specific
	tools (Web service monitor, Web service admin) when inserted into
	the xml via the pfx:webserviceconsole tag (automatically disabled
	in production mode)

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/WebServiceTask.java:
	Now only checks for server skeleton if there's something to do

	* example/common/conf/server-config.wsdd: Removed setting of
	attachments.Directory, so WEB-INF/attachments should be taken
	as default

