2004-10-06  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* just some cosmetics

2004-10-05  Martin Leidig  <mleidig@schlund.de>

	Added webservice support to Pustefix, which now makes it possible
	to exchange data/access application state via SOAP by providing
	special webservice capabilities. This is done by a close webservice
	server integration on the server side (with Apache Axis as default
	server) and a client side Javascript SOAP implementation supporting
	all important browsers (with some special features, like automatically
	generated Javascript webservice stubs).

	Added webservice libraries (Apache Axis and dependent libraries):

	* lib/axis-ant.jar
	* lib/axis.jar
	* lib/commons-discovery.jar
	* lib/commons-logging.jar
	* lib/jaxrpc.jar
	* lib/saaj.jar
	* lib/wsdl4j.jar

	Added WSDL processing library (for stub generation):

	* lib/wsif.jar

	Added special webservice task for generation of descriptors and code:
	* build.xml

	Added webservice targets, e.g. "webservice-config" for building
	webservice configuration, "webservice" for building WSDL, WSDD and stub
	files:
	* skel/build.xml

	Added xml schema, defining the webservice configuration (server and
	services):
	* example/core/schema/wsconfig200401.xsd

	Added copy (to site) instruction for webservice configuration schema:
	* maven.xml

	Added catalog entry for webservice configuration schema:
	* example/core/schema/catalog.xml

	Added webservice logger, customized Axis and apache.commons Digester
	logging (see comment within this file):
	* example/common/conf/pfixlog.xml.in

	Added axis webservice deployment descriptor skeleton:
	* example/common/conf/server-config.wsdd

	Added stylesheet for creating webservice.conf from customizable
	webservice.conf.in:
	* example/core/build/create_webservice.xsl

	Added javascript SOAP 1.1 (RPC/Encoded) implementation
	* example/core/script/webservice.js

	Added platform independent javascript XMLHttpRequest implementation
	* example/core/script/xml.js

	Added webservice example application, containing some demos and tests
	* example/webservice

	Roundup of the most important webservice application files:

	Webservice configuration, containing global server settings and
	definitions of some demo and test services:
	* example/webservice/conf/webservice.conf.in

	Some examples provide usage of different clientside soap
	calling mechanisms, which are placed in files with the a naming
	convention (SERVICE-pfxsoap.js for the Pustefix Javascript SOAP
	implementation, SERVICE-soap.js for Mozilla Low Level SOAP and
	SERVICE-wsdl.js for Mozilla WSDL proxying), example:
	* example/webservice/htdocs/calc-pfxsoap.js
	* example/webservice/htdocs/calc-soap.js
	* example/webservice/htdocs/calc-wsdl.js

	Added webservice example classes (webservice interfaces and
	implementations, beans, etc.). The service classes follow an optional
	naming convention (SERVICE.java for interfaces and SERVICEImpl.java
	for the according implementation), example:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/webservices/Calculator.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/example/webservices/CalculatorImpl.java

	Added lots of classes, only the important ones will be listed and
	shortly described:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice: Main package, containing general
	webservice classes, important classes:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/AbstractService.java: Base class
	of all service implementations, which need access to the application
	state (ContextResources),
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceContext.java: Class,
	which provides access to webservice container internals (i.e. service
	configuration), similar to Servlet API's ServletContext
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/WebServiceServlet.java: This class
	extends AxisServlet from the Axis distribution to provide additional
	features and smoothly integrate Axis into Pustefix.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config: Package, containing all
	the stuff for configuration reading and management, important classes:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/Configuration.java: Main
	configuration class, providing access to Webservice container and
	webservices configuration
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/GlobalServiceConfig.java:
	Manages global/container configuration
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/config/ServiceConfig.java:
	Manages service configuration

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate: Package, containing all
	the stuff for creation of deployment descriptors, WSDL and code
	generation, important classes:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/WebServiceTask.java: Ant
	task, which generates descriptors, WSDL and code (and is responsible
	for deploying them to the according webapplication), using the
	following subtasks:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Java2Wsdl.java: Generates
	WSDL descriptions from Java interfaces
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Wsdl2Java.java: Generates
	WSDD deployment descriptors from WSDL descriptions
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/generate/Wsdl2Js.java: Generates
	Javascript SOAP stubs from WSDL descriptions

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler: Package, containing
	Message handlers, working as interceptors during SOAP Message
	processing, important classes:

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/AbstractHandler.java: Base
	class for handlers which provides methods to access servlet-/webservice
	context and request.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/AuthenticationHandler.java:
	Handler, which is responsible for handling the different authentication
 	mechanisms, e.g. authentication via Pustefix session and calling
	checkAuthorization on context
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/handler/MonitoringHandler.java:
	Handler, which intercepts message processing, to provide monitoring
	capabilities

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/webservice/monitor: Package, implementing
	message monitoring capabilities (message history)

2004-10-04  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/editor/handlers/ImagesUploadHandler.java:
	Now creates directories for a file, if neccessary directories do not exist yet.

