2004-08-09  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Path.java (create(File file)): new method,
	this will use the parent dir of the file argument as the Path base.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xslt.java: only one interface to the
	load Templates objects remains. For every "base directory"
	(usually one currently) there will be a new factory created with
	it's own FileResolver. The class uses the Path class more consitently.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/util/Xml.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/testenv/TestcaseStepResult.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/XSLVirtualTarget.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/XSLLeafTarget.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/VirtualTarget.java:
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: only use the new
	interface of Xslt.java

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/util/XsltTransformer.java: reenabled a
	private factory and transformation for now. We need to check how
	to rewrite it again to use the new, smaller interface of Xslt.java

