2004-07-05  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* lib/rmiobj.jar: removed
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/util/ExceptionDataValue.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/util/ExceptionDataValueHelper.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/util/ExceptionDataValueVisitor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/util/TextCreatorVisitor.java
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/util/XMLCreatorVisitor.java

2004-07-02  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* example/core/xsl/xmlfontify.xsl.in: new file to fontify the xml-only output,
	as not all browsers seem to be able to display a DOM tree view.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java: really render the
	saved DOM, not only serializing to text/xml

2004-07-02  Michael Hartmier  <mhm@schlund.de>
	* project.properties, project.xml: maven build files

2004-07-01  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/UniversalExceptionProcessor.java:
	ensure, that exception is also printed in logfile.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PerfEventTypeConfig.java: more logging if
	init  failed.
	* lib/rmiobj.jar: new jar with exception-formatting utilities.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PerfEventTypeConfig.java: new class
	getting delay times from factory.prop.in
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PerfEventType.java: adjusted to
	above changes.
	* example/common/conf/factory.prop.in: added delays for perf-logging.

2004-06-30  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PerfEventType.java: new class
        for typed performance logging events.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PfixServletRequest.java:
         -added method endLogEntry(PerfEventType)
         -changed format of written perf-logfile
         -removed method getCreationTimestamp, now
        calling initPerfLog and startLogEntry in constructor
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java:
         -added method endLogEntry(PerfEventType)
         -adjusted perf-logging with typed perf-events.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java(doGet):
         -adjusted perf-logging with typed perf-events.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java(getDocument, process):
         -adjusted perf-logging with typed perf-events.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/DefaultIWrapperState.java(getDocument):
         -adjusted perf-logging with typed perf-events.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/StaticState.java(renderContextResources):
         -adjusted perf-logging with typed perf-events.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/app/IHandlerSimpleContainer.java(
	areHandlerActive, isPageAccessible, needsData):
         -adjusted perf-logging with typed perf-events.

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/PfixServletRequest.java:
	prevent logging by doing nothing if not PFXPERF.isDebugEnabled
	in initPerfLog, startLogEntry, endLogEntry, printLog

2004-06-23  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java (flowBeforeNeedsData):
	fixed stupid bug.

2004-06-22  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixcore/workflow/Context.java (flowBeforeNeedsData):
	fixed an instance where it was possible that needsData() would be called on the handlers
	despite the fact that the whole page was inaccessible because of a prerequisitesMet() call
	returning true.

2004-06-22  Adam Habermann  <adam.habermann@schlund.de>

	* build.xml, skel/build.xml:
	target "compile": now passing ant property "javac.nowarn" to attribute
	nowarn of task javac.

2004-06-22  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* released 0.6.3, started 0.6.4-pre

2004-06-22  Benjamin Reitzammer <benjamin@schlund.de>

	* example/core/build/create_tomcatweb.xsl
	If you set project/includeexternalwebxml/@include to 'true' a web.xml that
	lies in the project's conf directory will be included into the final web.xml
	that's the result of the transformation. No checks regarding validity (beyond
	well-formedness) are performed on the included configuration.


2004-06-21  Joerg Haecker <haecker@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/AbstractXMLServer.java(handleDocument):
	Do not catch TargetGenerationExcpetions any more, they
	be processed by a defined ExceptionProcessor.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/targets/TargetGenerationException.java: minor changes.
	* example/core/xsl/errorrepresentation.xsl.in: stylesheet for rendering errors on screen.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/UniversalExceptionProcessor.java:
	ExceptionProcessor rendering errors on screen.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java(callProcess):
	- if there is no processor defined for the passed throwable, use the old
	  exceptionhandler.
	- check if the passed throwable is an instance of the defined
	  throwable. If true, use the defined processor.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/ExceptionProcessor.java:
	added  parameter properties to the processException-method.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/PageForwardingExceptionProcessor.java:
	adjusted to above changes.
	* example/common/conf/pustefix.prop.in: added
	UniversalExceptionProcessor for all Throwables in test-mode.
	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/exceptionprocessor/ExceptionDataValueHelper.java:
	added new helper class.
	* lib/rmiobj.jar: added jar with value-objects and helper classes.

2004-06-21  Jens Lautenbacher  <jtl@schlund.de>

	* src/de/schlund/pfixxml/ServletManager.java: fixed generated property
	__PROPERTIES_LOAD_INDEX to really get incremented every time the
	properties are reloaded.

